ys.succinct.xml.parser

Class SuccinctDocumentBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder
      • ys.succinct.xml.parser.SuccinctDocumentBuilder

  • public class SuccinctDocumentBuilder
extends DocumentBuilder
    A builder that produces the succinct Document from the XML input. The builder relies on capabilities that the underlying StAX parser provides, therefore there are some restrictions.

    The following Node types are not supported:

    • DocumentType (DTD isn't parsed)
    • Entity
    • EntityReference (entity references are resolved by default)
    • Notation (DTD isn't parsed).

    The following handlers are not supported:

    • EntityResolver
    • ErrorHandler.

    The succinct Document that the parser produces is read-only. This means that the mutation and creation API isn't supported also.

    The size of XML document that the builder can handle is restricted by the heap space and succinct data structure limits. Practically, the number of nodes that the succinct DOM can support doesn't exceed Integer.MAX_VALUE / 2.

    Author:
    Yauheni Shahun
